other_tests.findings: The gallbladder is noted to be distended with circumferential wall edema, with surrounding fat stranding; possible small high density seen in the neck of the gallbladder which may represent a stone. The liver shows no focal lesion or intrahepatic biliary dilatation. The spleen is mildly enlarged, measuring up to 14 cm in length. No evidence of obstruction in the small and large intestine.
